Reconnaissance Tools
Amass: A tool for in-depth DNS enumeration.
Sublist3r: Fast subdomain enumeration tool.
Recon-ng: A web reconnaissance framework.
Shodan: A search engine for Internet-connected devices.
Censys: Another search engine for discovering devices and services on the Internet.
Web Application Testing Tools
Burp Suite: A comprehensive web vulnerability scanner with various features like proxy, scanner, intruder, repeater, and more. The community edition is free, while the professional edition offers advanced capabilities.
OWASP ZAP: An open-source web application security scanner.
SQLmap: An automated tool for detecting and exploiting SQL injection flaws.
Wfuzz: A tool for brute-forcing web applications.
Nikto: A web server scanner that tests for various vulnerabilities.
Network Testing Tools
Nmap: A network scanning tool to discover hosts and services.
Wireshark: A network protocol analyzer to capture and inspect network traffic.
Metasploit: A penetration testing framework that includes various exploits and payloads.
Fuzzing Tools
ffuf: A fast web fuzzer for finding hidden directories and files.
Dirbuster: A tool to brute-force directories and files on web servers.
Wfuzz: Can also be used for directory and file brute-forcing.
Mobile Application Testing Tools
MobSF (Mobile Security Framework): An automated mobile app security testing framework.
Frida: A dynamic instrumentation toolkit for performing custom analysis.
Jadx: A tool for decompiling Android applications.
Source Code Review Tools
Semgrep: A tool for static analysis and finding vulnerabilities in code.
Bandit: A tool to find common security issues in Python code.
FindSecBugs: A security-focused static analysis tool for Java applications.
Exploitation and Post-Exploitation Tools
Metasploit: As mentioned, useful for exploitation and post-exploitation.
Empire: A post-exploitation framework that uses PowerShell and Python.
Responder: A tool to poison LLMNR, NBT-NS, and MDNS to gather network credentials.
Miscellaneous Tools
Ghidra: A software reverse engineering framework.
Radare2: A set of utilities for binary analysis.
CyberChef: A web app for encryption, encoding, compression, and data analysis.
Browser Extensions
Wappalyzer: Identifies technologies used on websites.
Shodan Plugin: Shows Shodan data for the current website.
HackBar: Helps with manual testing for SQL injections, XSS, and other vulnerabilities.
Keeping Organized
Trello or Notion: For organizing and tracking your findings and progress.
KeepNote or CherryTree: For note-taking during your recon and testing.
Learning Resources
PortSwigger Web Security Academy: For practical exercises on web vulnerabilities.
HackerOne Hacktivity: To see disclosed reports and learn from others.
Bugcrowd University: Offers various resources and courses to improve your skills.
